# ASK 2.0 - Kconfig (out-of-tree)
#
# PR1: skeleton config. Hard dependencies on FSL_DPAA / CAAM_QI / etc.
# will be tightened in later PRs as the corresponding subsystems start
# referencing those facilities.

config NET_ASK
tristate "ASK 2.0 hardware-accelerated forwarding (LS1046A)"
depends on NET
depends on ARM64 || COMPILE_TEST
default n
help
  ASK 2.0 ("Anti-Strawberry-Kiwi") is a clean-room reimplementation of
  the legacy ASK 1.x flow/IPsec offload stack for the NXP LS1046A
  Mono Gateway DK using mainline DPAA1 / CAAM drivers and standard
  Linux callback infrastructure (nf_flow_table, xfrmdev_ops,
  flow_block_cb).

  Exposes a generic-netlink family ("ask") for userspace askd(8) to
  query and configure the offload datapath.

  PR1 is a skeleton: registers the genl family and answers
  ASK_CMD_GET_INFO. No flows are accelerated yet.

  See specs/ask-2.0-rewrite-spec.md for the full architecture.

  Say M here to build as a module (recommended). Say N if unsure.